  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Taijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This jutsu can only be cast as a Taijutsu <em><strong>Finisher</strong></em>. You inhale and take a charging stance, manifesting ripples of fire release chakra throughout your entire body. You cover your fist in flames and then release it as it explodes in the shape of a falcon. Make a melee taijutsu attack against the creature dealing unarmed damage + 10d10 fire damage and knocking them back 30 feet on a hit. If a creature knocked back by this jutsu collides with a solid object, their movement is stopped, taking falling damage equal to the distance they would have fallen.</p><p>Regardless of a hit or miss, all creatures excluding you and your original target, within 5 feet must make a Dexterity saving throw taking 8d6 fire damage on a failed save.</p>",
